{
  "message": "fix(home): add iOS safe area inset handling for mobile CTA\n\nProblem\n-------\nOn iPhones with home indicator (no physical button), the fixed mobile\nCTA button at the bottom overlapped with the system UI area, making\nit difficult to tap.\n\nSolution\n--------\nUse CSS environment variables to respect the safe-area-inset-bottom:\n\n1. Main container padding:\n   `pb-[calc(6rem+env(safe-area-inset-bottom))]`\n   Ensures content doesn't get hidden behind the fixed CTA + home indicator\n\n2. Mobile CTA positioning:\n   `bottom-[calc(1rem+env(safe-area-inset-bottom))]`\n   Lifts the button above the home indicator area\n\n3. Touch optimization:\n   Added `touch-manipulation` to prevent double-tap zoom delay\n\nThe env() values are only applied on iOS devices; on other platforms\nthey evaluate to 0, leaving the original 1rem/6rem spacing intact.\n\n\ud83e\udd16 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
